          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "This also seems to be one of the looting place not an educational institution, who only work for themselves only. They charge money on higher side as an  Admission fee as well as never refund you that. It seems to be their right to charge as a penalty for not to take an admission, although you haven't attend the class for a day. They makes lots of efforts to take the fee too much earlier then the batch starting date. But will refund  only security amount according their rules. So plz try to save yourself to trust on them and don't pay the fee in the advance. They have a gret team to trap you and will entertain only till you will pay the fee. Otherwise their attitude will be completely opposite then the beginning. So think 1000 times before pay the and take an admission.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Jayshree Periwal High School - Chitrakoot"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Jaideep Sumal"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-03-26",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "As a parent of a child studying in Jayshree Periwal High School (JPHS), I have experienced and observed, my decision of admitting him to JPHS has been wise. The way JPHS is managed and functioning, I feel my child is in the best hands in moulding him for a bright future.\nThe management team has vast experience on how the educational system in India is transforming and how to infuse those changing aspects gradually into the curriculum. The Principal and support staff are working hard with the highest level of professionalism in implementing the policies on ground. We highly appreciate the way they accommodate parents' demands and requests with a humane touch and being in direct communication with them 24*7.\nAs a parent, I would like my child to have an all round development of his personality. Whether studies, sports, Public speaking, social behaviour, respect for customs & traditions, becoming a responsible citizen. Outside the family, school is a place where a child learns the majority of his personal development skills. I feel, JPHS is an institution  which is taking care of these aspects well enough. The careful grooming and polishing of my child's personality is evident in just a few years since he joined it.  We have the highest level of gratitude and respect for the management and staff of JPHS in grooming my child.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
